The longer you use JMock, the more you begin to think about all the
things you can do by introducing object impostors.  I&#39;ve written this
on a project recently:

public void testForException() {
assertThrownException(isA(SomeException.class)).when(something).doSomethingThatShouldThrowException();
}

This is still magic, but the magic is in the API, rather than the test
runner.  I&#39;m genuinely curious if you, dear reader, like this better.

